<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <head>
        <link href="../../../../TableStyles/Shared/Fancy.css" rel="stylesheet" MadCap:stylesheetType="table" />
    </head>
    <body>
        <ol>
            <li>Select <span class="Emphasis">View &gt; SharePoint Explorer</span>. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare-Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../Flare/Interface/Window-Panes/SharePoint-Explorer.htm">SharePoint Explorer</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
            <li>
                <p>Locate the file that you want to open. You can use the "multi-view" to do this.</p>
                <MadCap:snippetBlock src="Multi-View-Table.flsnp" />
            </li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../../All/General/Do-One-Following.flsnp" />
                <ul>
                    <li>Double-click the file.</li>
                    <li>Right-click the file and select <span class="Emphasis">Open</span>.</li>
                    <li>Click on the file, and in the local toolbar click <img src="../../../../Images/Shared/Co-Fl-Li/Interface/Buttons/Open-btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>If it is a file type not supported in <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" />, you will be directed to open the file in its default application.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>